=== Etymology ===
Fr. [[Greek|Gk.]] ''delta'', the letter D.

=== Noun ===
# The fourth letter of the [[w:Greek alphabet|Greek Alphabet]], preceded by [[gamma]] ('''[[Γ]]''', '''[[γ]]''') and followed by [[epsilon]]('''[[Ε]]''', '''[[ε]]''').
#The triangular mouth of a large river that empties into a sea or large body of water.
#'''&#948;''' ''Phonetics.'' In the [[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]], the symbol that represents the voiced dental fricative. Usu. represented by the Icelandic [[eth|eth/edh]] (ð).
# (''mathematics'') A change in some quantity.
# (''computing, colloquial'') A small but noticeable effect.
#: ''This will slow the main code path down, but only by delta.''
# The letter ''D'' in the [[ICAO spelling alphabet]]

